HEADWORD: Bourdon
<hw>Bour"don</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>burdo</ets> mule, esp. one used for carrying litters. Cf. Sp.
<ets>muleta</ets> a young she mule; also, crutch, prop.]</ety> <def>A
pilgrim's staff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bourdon</ent>⟦br⟧
